metadata.name: Puzzles & Mysteries #123
metadata.description:
Nothing is true to reality about this piece.
Not the sky, nor the hills and definitely not the colors. 
It’s all about getting lost in a place we don’t know - A puzzle, a mystery and collecting the missing pieces.

Press “s” to save as png.

Made with p5js;

metadata.name: Contort #238
metadata.description:
Contort is the result of combining several previously meaningless experiments and learnings into a single cohesive algorithm. The project comes in a variety of shapes, bends, twists, colors, and other variations.  

The artwork builds towards the end-result by rendering a fixed number of forms per frame to ensure a smooth rendering process. Rendering times can vary depending on which features are combined by the hash.

metadata.name: geometric tiles #48
metadata.description:
Hello everyone, this is my first fxhash project.

There are three types of mints you can get: checkers, stairs and rectangular prisms - there is equal chance of getting any of those. 

There is also 8% chance of getting the rarity mint which is the mint with the grainy effect over it. However, you should check my twitter out in order to see the preview of all the mint types you can get.

The inspiration behind this project was M.C. Escher.

metadata.name: the way back home #237
metadata.description: Freeways lead to highways. Smaller highways lead to local roads. Which in turn lead to ever smaller streets, alleyways, and paths. Ultimately they will lead you home, if you are fortunate enough to find your way.
